  "description": [
    "26 DR WU DESCRIBES NATIONALISTSAIMS Minister Designate to U S in Harvard Club Address Out lines Reforms Affected The aspirations of the Nationalist government of China were described to the Washington Harvard Club last eve ning by Dr C C W r u minister desig nate to the United States from the new ly established government Chief Jus j tice Walter I McCoy of the District Supreme Court presided at the meet ing at the University Club Reforms effected by the Nationalists were outlined by Dr Wu who said the present period of Chinese history is reoegnized by Nationalist leaders as one of tutelage in which the greatest work is to dissipate the illiteracy prevailing among 85 per cent of the people The placing of censors and examiners one equal rank with the executive judi cial and legislative branches of the gov ernment was mentioned by Dr Wu as typical of the reforms brought about For 4000 years examiners had been em ployed by the Emperor The positions now are independent of political con trol he said which means that appli cants for governmental positions are judged according to impartial examina tions The function of censors simi larly appointed under"
